---

## About The Project

This is a professional hospital website. It features a modern, trust-focused design using a navy and gold color scheme, smooth scroll animations, and a fully responsive layout that works across all screen sizes.

---

## Sections

- **Hero** — Full-screen landing with headline, stats, and CTA buttons
- **Services / Departments** — 6 medical departments displayed in a CSS Grid layout
- **Doctors / Team** — 4 specialist doctor cards with ratings and experience
- **Appointment Booking** — Working form with department selection and confirmation feedback
- **Contact & Location** — Address, phone, email, and opening hours

---

## Built With

- HTML5
- CSS3 (Grid, Flexbox, Custom Properties, Animations)
- JavaScript (scroll reveal, mobile nav, form interaction)
- Google Fonts — Playfair Display + DM Sans

---

## Key Features

- Mobile-first responsive design with breakpoints at 480px, 768px, and 1024px
- Fixed navbar with blur backdrop and mobile hamburger menu
- Scroll-triggered fade-in animations via IntersectionObserver
- CSS Grid named areas for the two-column layout sections
- Interactive booking form with loading and success state feedback
- No frameworks or dependencies — zero build step required

---

## What I Learned

- Structuring a multi-section single-page layout from scratch
- CSS Grid for complex two-column sections
- Using `IntersectionObserver` for scroll animations without JavaScript libraries
- Building a responsive navbar with a working mobile menu
- Designing for trust — color psychology and layout choices for healthcare

